   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legal Aid for Victims of Domestic Violence in SA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lawyers against Abuse (LvA) provides free legal services and psycho-social support to victims of sexual and domestic violence in one of South Africa&apos;s most disadvantaged communities. Diepsloot, an informal settlement north of Johannesburg, is home to over 500,000 people, yet LvA is the only organization of its kind working in the community. LvA also works closely with local police and courts to ensure victims of gender-based violence are treated with dignity and respect when seeking justice.</narrative>
  </description>
